      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's a good start. specifically, i want to tackle the meritocracy argument that critics usually bring up. they always say things like \"people should just work harder\" or that wealth is earned through merit. can you help me write a section that refutes that? i want to show how the meritocracy concept is basically a fallacy in the context of systemic racism and how it's used to justify existing inequalities. maybe frame it as a way to deconstruct that specific myth?",
